text: Yuma County is a county in the southwestern part of the U.S. state of Arizona. As of the 2020 census, 203,881 people lived there. The county seat is Yuma. The county borders three states: Sonora, Mexico, to the south, and two other states to the west, across the Colorado River: California of the United States and the Mexican state of Baja California. ==References== Category:Arizona counties Category:1864 establishments in the United States Category:1860s establishments in Arizona Territory
title: Yuma County, Arizona
